tasks.details:
1. Create HealthController class in com.taskmaster.backend.controller package
2. Annotate with @RestController
3. Implement GET endpoint:
   @GetMapping("/api/health")
   public ResponseEntity<Map<String, String>> health() {
       Map<String, String> response = new HashMap<>();
       response.put("status", "UP");
       response.put("timestamp", Instant.now().toString());
       return ResponseEntity.ok(response);
   }
4. Ensure endpoint is accessible at http://localhost:8080/api/health
5. Configure CORS to allow frontend requests during development

1. Modify vite.config.js to include proxy configuration:
   export default defineConfig({
     plugins: [react()],
     server: {
       proxy: {
         '/api': {
           target: 'http://localhost:8080',
           changeOrigin: true,
           secure: false
         }
       }
     }
   })
2. Ensure proxy routes all /api/* requests to backend server
3. Test proxy configuration by starting both servers
4. Verify no CORS errors occur when making requests to /api endpoints
